  "# chain\n\n## answer\n\nchain\n[tʃeɪn]\nn. 链（条）；［pl.］镣铐；一连串，一系列（serial）；连锁店 vt. 用链条拴住；联号，连锁店\nAlgae are the base of the aquatic food chain, which means the other organisms depend on them for food.<br>With bicycle chains covered, cyclists would need to clean and oil their chains only once every six months instead of once a week.<br>If that toad became extinct, we'd lose an important link in the chain of revolution.\n水藻是水生食物链的基础，也就是说其他生物依靠它们获得食物。<br>盖住自行车链条，骑车的人只需半年而非一周给链条清洗并上油一次。<br>如果那种蟾蜍灭绝了，我们将失去进化链上重要的一环。\n\n\nchain reaction 连锁反应\n\n\n\n\nWord List 36\n",
  "# monotonous\n\n## answer\n\nmonotonous\n[məˈnɑːtənəs]\na. 单调的，无聊的（＊boring, ＊tedious）\nFactory work is less creative and more monotonous.\n在工厂工作更缺乏创意，更加单调。\n\n词根记忆：mono（单个）＋ton（声音）＋ous→一个声音的→单调的\n\n\n\n\n\nWord List 36\n",
