  "# distinguish\n\n## answer\n\ndistinguish\n[dɪˈstɪŋɡwɪʃ]\nv. 区别，辨别（＊discriminate, differentiate）；使有别于，成为…的特征；看清，听出；使杰出，使著名\nThese three kinds of meteorites can usually be distinguished by density.\n这三种陨星通常可以通过密度来区别。\n\n词根记忆：di（分开）＋sting（刺）＋uish→用刺将…分开→区别，辨别\ndistinguish from 区别，识别；distinguish oneself 使自己脱颖而出\ndistinguishable（a. 可区别的；易辨认的）；distinguished（a. 著名的；高贵的）\n\n\n\nWord List 36\n",
