  "# economic\n\n## answer\n\neconomic\n[ˌiːkəˈnɑːmɪk]\na. 经济的；经济上的；经济学的；合算的\nIn order to comprehend the operation of an economic system, we must deal not only with the things that can be seen, but we also have to give our attention to the things which cannot be perceived directly.<br>In the economic sense, laisser faire meant that while the government should be responsible for things like maintaining peace and protecting property rights, it should not interfere with private business.\n为全面理解经济体制的运作，我们不但要面对可见的问题，而且要关注不能直接被察觉的问题。<br>从经济学上讲，自由主义指政府应该在为诸如维护秩序和保护产权这些事务负责的同时，不应干预私营企业。\n\n词根记忆：eco（家）＋nom（管理）＋ic→管理家庭开支的→经济的\neconomic conditions 经济情况\nuneconomic（a. 不经济的，浪费的）\n\n\n\nWord List 46\n",
